p.span: Here we depict the primordial relationship between industrial production and capital. There are four dimensions: 1. Generation of new capital from the mining profits; 2. Extraction of private wealth for consumption. 3. Reallocation of wealth to stimulate innovation in related supply chains; 4. State attachment for supporting infrastructure. Note that the relationship between the Steam Pumps and Coal Mining Company is inside a Production Network.
